data.name: tbHelp.Text
data.value:
# Bottom panel: [F10] Connect - connect/disconnect button, clicked while holding Ctrl key initializes SIMULATION MODE for selected ECU. Please remember to first press F10 key/click Connect button and then turn ON the ignition when requested.
# Settings tab: Select ECU - select Engine Control Unit type which is appropriate for your car. You may also use the Automatic Detection. Select COM - select the COM Port or the Virtual COM Port of your RS-232/USB Diagnostic Interface. Supported interface type is ISO-KKL also known as VAG-COM 409-1 Clone. If you use USB interface please make sure that it is connected to the USB port BEFORE you start the IAW Scan 2 application. LOG Enabled - enable logging diagnostic session to a file IESlog_<date_time> located in the LOG folder under the application folder. Compatible mode - add extra 4ms delay between receiving response from ECU and sending next request to ECU.
# Parameters tab: Use checkbox on the left to turn on polling selected parameter, you may also press the A key/button to select all parameters, or press N key/button to remove selection from all parameters. Parameters checked individually are added to Trace list of the Graphs tab as checked, but when you add all parameters using A key/button, parameters will be added to Traces list as unchecked. Please note that the more parameters you select the lower refresh rate will be. Query errors - enable quering errors while parameters are displayed, this will reduce the parameters refresh rate but errors will be logged to a file.
# Errors tab: List presents stored, validated and active errors and their reason where available. The MIL checkbox indicates whether particular error lit the MIL lamp. In the IAW-x6F ECU it is possible that MIL lamp is lit while no listed error has checked checkbox in the MIL column - this is a case when error was present and stored during current ECU power cycle, but is no longer active. There are three (in IAW-x6F two) error states possible: @ Active - error is present at the moment. @ Verified - error is/was present long enough, during current ECU power cycle, to be memorized (not available in IAW-x6F). @ Stored - error has been verified during previous ECU power cycle (for IAW-x6F it is a sum of Verified and Stored). Clear button - press C key or push this button to clear stored errors from ECU.
# Tests tab: List presents available tests for current ECU. Please note that some modules are optional and may be not present in your car. Also note that staus PASSED does not mean that the component is fully functional. Tests are only to activate selected component so the car mechanic may observe the component if it is working correctly or not. Execute button - press E key or push this button to execute currently selected test.
# Graphs tab: Trace - list of available parameters, you may select which parameters would you like to be recorded on a graph and in a CSV file. Please note that it is strongly recommended to select only these parameters which you like to record on a Parameters Tab. Start button - press S key or push this button to start/stop recording selected parameters. Along with the graph also the CSV file is created with the recorded data. The file is named IESexp_<date_time> and is located in the LOG folder under the application folder.
